		<div id="comment_body_64285572">Depends what you want the AI to do for you. For example current LLMs can be fruitfully thought of as a natural language interface. They are like an intermediate language that sits between you and more traditional tools and translates your natural language query into concrete instructions for the traditional tools. This is great for beginners.
<p>
If you're not a beginner, it's a terrible idea. Natural language is extremely imprecise and you have to jump through crazy hoops to have any chance to communicate som<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
